Definition 1. We say that $K\colon\mathcal{C}\to\sigma\mathcal{C}$ is a Katětov functor if • $K$ is a covariant functor, • there is a natural transformation $\{\eta_{x}\}_{x\in\mathcal{C}}$ between $id_{\mathcal{C}}$ and $K$, $\xymatrix{x\ar[d]_{f}\ar[rr]^{\eta_{x}}&&K(x)\ar[d]^{K(f)}\\ y\ar[rr]_{\eta_{y}}&&K(y)}$ • every one point extension $y\in\mathcal{C}$ of $x\in\mathcal{C}$ is realized in $K(x)$ over $\eta_{x}(x)$. $\xymatrix{x\ar[d]\ar[rr]&&K(x)\\ y\ar[rru]&&}$
