Definition 5.3. In the subcategory $\mathfrak{A}^{\simCat^{\mathrm{op}}}_{f}$ of $\mathfrak{A}^{\simCat^{\mathrm{op}}}$ a cofibration $f:X\to Y$ is if there is a $g:Y\to X$ such that $g\circ f=\id_{X}$ and an $h:\Delta[1]\times Y\to Y$ such that $h\circ k=(\id_{Y},f\circ g)$ if $k:1+1\to\Delta[1]$ is the cycle inclusion and $h\circ(\id_{\Delta[1]}\times f)=f\circ\pi_{1}$. $\xymatrix{Y+Y\ar[d]_{k\times\id}\ar[dr]^{(\id,f\circ g)}\\ \Delta[1]\times Y\ar[r]_{(}.6)h&Y\\ \Delta[1]\times X\ar[r]_{(}.6){\pi_{1}}\ar[u]^{\id\times f}&X\ar[u]_{f}\\ }$
